descriptionHtml:
Croatia won third place in the 1998 World Cup in France. The Croatian national football team is under the auspices of Hrvatski Nogometni Savez (HNS) or the Croatian Football Olympics. The country that gave birth to Davor Suker first appeared in the World Cup in 1998. In the World Cup held in France, it was very good to score 2-1. The Croatian national team returned to competing in the 2002 and 2006 World Cups. At the 2010 World Cup, Croatia no longer qualified and only returned to playing in the 2014 and 2018 World Cups.

Croatia's success in qualifying for Russia this year cannot be separated from the cold hands of coach Zlatko Dalic. After bringing Al-Ain to become runner-up of the 2016 Asian Champions League, Dalic was appointed to coach the Croatian national team in the period October 2017. He replaced Ante Cacic who was sacked. In fact, at that time Croatia left a crucial final match against Ukraine. At the 2018 World Cup held in Russia, the team raised by Zlatko Dalic was in Group D with Iceland, Nigeria and Argentina. Creating the best achievements in the European Cup, which reached the quarter-finals in the 1996 European Cup and 2008. Until 2018, Croatia has qualified for the European Cup 5 times.

World cup qualifiers are:
Group A: Russia (host country), Saudi Arabia, Egypt and Uruguay.
GROUP B: Portugal, Spain, Morocco and Iran.
GROUP C: France, Australia, Peru and Denmark.
GROUP D: Argentina, Iceland, Croatia & Nigeria.
GROUP E: Brazil, Switzerland, Costa Rica, and Serbia.
GROUP F, Germany, Mexico, Sweden, Korea Republic.
GROUP G: Belgium, Panama, Tunisia, England.
